subject: JUnit 3.8.2 released
msgSnippet: All, JUnit 3.8.2 has been released, and is available from SourceForge: http://sourceforge.net/projects/junit/ The changes between 3.8.1 and 3.8.2 are minimal,
messageBody:
All,

JUnit 3.8.2 has been released, and is available from SourceForge:

http://sourceforge.net/projects/junit/

The changes between 3.8.1 and 3.8.2 are minimal, and the focus was on
fixing the accumulated bug reports. The most significant change is
replacing the much-reviled string comparison format with something
easier to read and use. For more details, see the included README.html

For the latest, most extensible and most usable JUnit ever, developers
should download and use JUnit 4.0.

Thanks,

David Saff
